>> [summary by Robert Eachus]
>  Nice... but does it work?

The procedure Mr. Eachus pointed out is mentioned in Judy Moore's
paper "Protocol Failures in Cryptosystems", which in turn references a
paper by DeLaurentis "A further weakness in the common modulus
protocol...", Cryptologia, July 1984.  

As Robert said, knowledge of one encryption/decrytion pair of
exponents for a given modulus gives rise to a probablistic algorithm
for factoring the modulus.  The expected number of trials before
success is no greater than 2.

So check out DeLaurentis' paper.

